{
  "text": "When the \u00a5{me plasmids from both the poultry and human isolates were introduced into S. typhimurium phage type 36, which is lysed by all the S. typhimurium typing phages, the resultant phage restriction patterns matched that previously described as non-conforming, type 10 (NC10) [CITATION_1] . This restriction pattern is typical of that produced by plasmids of the F : me incompatibility group.",
  "citation_candidates": [
